**Segments**

- Based on resin type, the packaging adhesives market can be segmented into water-based, solvent-based, hot melt, and others. Water-based adhesives are environmentally friendly and offer excellent bond strength. Solvent-based adhesives provide quick drying and strong adhesion, but their use is declining due to environmental concerns. Hot melt adhesives have fast setting times and are widely used in packaging applications.

- On the basis of technology, the market can be categorized into flexography, lithography, digital printing, screen printing, and others. Flexography is commonly used for printing on packaging materials like cardboard and plastic. Lithography offers high-quality printing suitable for intricate designs. Digital printing provides flexibility and customization options for packaging designs.

- In terms of application, the packaging adhesives market can be divided into food & beverage, pharmaceuticals, electronics, consumer goods, and others. The food & beverage industry is a major consumer of packaging adhesives due to strict regulations on food safety and packaging durability. The pharmaceutical sector requires adhesives that adhere to stringent quality and safety standards.

